The $700 billion economic bailout bill, which is to be divided into several instalments and which aims to buy off poor bank loans, is already in writing.
Half the amount will be used in the first round.
After further negotiations, which ended on Saturday after midnight of American Eastern time, Congressional officials reached an agreement in a few days’ debate on a $700 billion bailout, Reuters said.
